#: ../../docs/technical/hstore-vs-jsonb.rst:47
msgid "HStore is more compact because it stores flat key-value pairs without structural overhead:"
msgstr "HStore es más compacto porque almacena pares clave-valor planos sin sobrecarga estructural:"

#: ../../docs/technical/hstore-vs-jsonb.rst:52
msgid "HStore: ~200 bytes for 10 key-value pairs"
msgstr "HStore: ~200 bytes para 10 pares clave-valor"

#: ../../docs/technical/hstore-vs-jsonb.rst:53
msgid "JSONB:  ~350 bytes for the same data (structure overhead)"
msgstr "JSONB: ~350 bytes para los mismos datos (sobrecarga estructural)"

